CATHAY
HOTEL
CABLE ADDRESS
CATHOTEL
SHANGHAI, CHINA.
Sunday April 23 33
Dearest Debs
Groeger, the lucky dog, has finished his
part
of our job in
China and is leaving tonight for home.
I am asking him to take this letter to you and to get
in touch with you in person as soon as
possible
to
tell you ab out our trip and
the present status of
negotiations. The cable ordering Groeger home came this
morning and
you never saw
a happier man in your life
than that Dutchman. Of course it has been a sad day for
me not that I will
mind missing G but the thought of
him
and his luck has made me plenty jealous and terr-
ibly homesic}.
I
am sending
some night gowns by G
which cost about $ 3.00
each. If they are any good
you can write me and I will get some more - better ones
if you like which cost about
twice as much but are very
elab orate. It was for that reason that I bought these.
Maybe you can give them away if they are no good. I am
also sending with the nighties some cock tail sets. I
am terribly sorry but I can not remember
whether
sent
the blue ones to Ruth
or to 4904.
Please send them all
out to Ma and ask her to get together with Ruth.
I have been very busy and believe have
made
some
real
progress. You see I was really unable to do any-
thing until the deal for the acquisition of China Air
by PAA on April lst.
Now am making
some real strides.
Had a
grand
party for the Doolittles Friday.
Everyone
said it was the best party which has been given. Had
lots of
people to whom I was under obligations. Dr. Fearn
the Hutchins, Howards, Jouetts, Arnolds and
others. All
seemed to enjoy the dinner and
dancing â€¢
Groeger and I
are now going over reports and
later I
will go out to
the boat with him to
say "good bye"
Lots and lots of love to
you and
kids -
Had
Che
the
P. S.
Also inclost hirt wet last of 12 dolie.
good luck!
latter
